d, the countries that have been part of a globally-linked rapid develop- ment process during the past two decades. India and Sri Lanka come next (Figure 7.2).They are at about the same level but the latter gets past the former by reporting significantly high- er values in availability- and efficiency-linked indicators. Immediately following them are Mongolia and Indonesia.These report medium level values in all the five categories of ICT development.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "25a361d5-bb28-4a79-afcf-79eec2813055": {"__data__": {"id_": "25a361d5-bb28-4a79-afcf-79eec2813055", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-2005-promoting-ict-human-development-asia-summary", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Asia-Pacific Human Development 2005: Promoting ICT for Human Development in Asia - Summary", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-2005-promoting-ict-human-development-asia-summary", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "b90c4dfbecc9e6d2cb8e6d788c03b12e378c74684d39acf1b35d6dc58e64309a"}, "2": {"node_id": "655fabeb-83a9-41b8-8f03-38c98e21c50d", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-2005-promoting-ict-human-development-asia-summary", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "259209ba506476eac336fda0fe